Comment:
 XBoing was originally written by Justin C. Kibell between 1993 and 1996
 as a blockout-style arcade game for the X Window System (Xlib + XPM).
 The 1996 sources are preserved verbatim in the original/ directory under
 their original X Consortium-style license.
 .
 The modernized SDL2 port (CMake build, src/, include/, tests/, packaging,
 documentation) is licensed under the MIT License.

